        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 4:27PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 11 miles southwest of Urbana to near
Junction City, or extending from 11 miles east of Junction City to
near Junction City, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Junction City, Bernice, Cooley, Wesson, Spearsville, Lillie,
Taylorville, Lockhart, Catesville, Corney Lake and Summerfield.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
